utional, it also has the salutary effect of forcing litigants to consider a more pressing question: Can sex work be rationalized as a criminal matter at all?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aSex workxLaw and legislationzCanada. 0aSex workersxLegal status, laws, etc.zCanada. 7aLAW / Constitutional.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140848408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140825540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486978240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774869782423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774869782/original  a978-3-11-140825-5  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  a978-3-11-140848-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles